    "hadith_number": "25",
    "english_translation": "Narrated by Matar from Ata' from Ubayd ibn Umayr that Umar ibn al-Khattab may Allah be pleased with him was giving a sermon at Mina. He saw a man on a mountain cutting down a tree, so he called him. He said: Do you not know that the trees of Makkah should not be cut, nor its vegetation grazed? He said: Yes, but my weak camel forced me (to do it). He said: So I was carried on a camel. He said: Do not repeat, and do not put anything on it",
